San_Rafael.Mailliard, California: Mailliard is a former settlement in Marin County, California. It was located on the Northwestern Pacific Railroad 8 miles (13 km) south-southwest of downtown Novato, at an elevation of 436 feet (133 m), in part of what is now Woodacre, in the San Geronimo Valley. Mailliard still appeared on maps as of 1914.
